@REM ************************************************************************
@REM *                          INTRODUCTION                                *
@REM ************************************************************************

@node "INTRO" "What this Program does..."

                               @{u}Introduction@{uu}

I'm using the new FAME-BBS System for about 3 years now, and as you all know,
validating New Users i.e. is a normal job, but if you only have to validate
one user and nothing more, it could be very ugly to enter the BBS only for
validating purposes. So I decided to write my own external UserEditor,
allowing me to work on any user without going in my BBS first. 

The decision to use MUI is simple, I don't like hardcoded programs, which
doesn't allow you to configure the Program-Outfit to i.e. use other fonts,
other images etc... Well, MUI is the right solution for this problem, as it 
is 100% user-configurable. On the other Hand, MUI allowing the coders not
to spent most of the Development Time in creating a GUI, but in developing
the program itself. Creating a MUI-Interface is sooo simple..it takes me 
three days to create the whole GUI for UserEditor!! So if you don't have MUI or
don't like it, sit down in front of your Computer and start creating a
standard GUI which looks familiar to the current GUI...happy guruing...:)
@endnode

@REM ************************************************************************
@REM *                    INSTALLATION PROCEDURE                            *
@REM ************************************************************************

@node "INSTALLATION" "How to install UserEditor"

                               @{u}Requirements@{uu}

 To use UserEditor, you need the following things:

 @{b}-@{ub} OS 3.0 or higher. OS 2.x Support is dropped forever!

 @{b}-@{ub} MUI V3.6 or higher, lower versions @{b}*WON'T*@{ub} work anymore!

 @{b}-@{ub} NList.mcc by Gilles Masson (any Version should work)

 @{b}-@{ub} Complete installed FAME-System with at least one user (SysOp)

 @{b}-@{ub} For localization you need locale.library v38+ or higher, otherwise the
   UserEditor uses the built-in language english.

 @{b}-@{ub} Some users to work on....;)

                               @{b}@{u}Installation@{uu}@{ub}

 Normally you would install UserEditor via the supplied Installerscript,
 this is also the recommended way to update the UserEditor. In this case, 
 everything is setup by the script and no user action is required. If you 
 wish to install it manually, please read the lines below for detailed 
 informations.

                            @{b}Manual Installation@{ub}

 When you have first installed the FAME-System, the UserEditor is copied
 into the @{fg fill}FAME:Modules/@{fg text} drawer. Also this Location is the default path set
 in '@{fg shine}SystemEditor->FAME Modules@{fg text}'. If you don't like this location, you could
 of course copy it to another location, but in fact that all external FAME
 modules where stored inside this drawer, it's the best location by far
 to have all files stored in the same place! If you change the installation
 path, please make sure to adjust also the path in the SystemEditor under
 FAME Modules!

 If you recieve an Update of the UserEditor, simply overwrite your existing
 version with the new one, and update also all other files supplied with the
 update archive of UserEditor.

 If you want to use UserEditor in your preffered language, copy the catalog-
 file of your language (if supplied) into this drawer:

                 @{fg fill}LOCALE:Catalogs/<language>/UserEd.catalog@{fg text}

 Alternativly you may also store the locale files in the program dir
 of UserEditor, in this case the drawer structure has to be:

                @{fg fill}PROGDIR:Catalogs/<language>/UserEd.catalog@{fg text}

 If you have choosen to install UserEditor to a different drawer
 like the default drawer '@{fg fill}FAME:Modules/@{fg text}', please check also if the path for 
 UserEditor set in '@{fg shine}SystemEditor/FAME Modules@{fg text}' points to the correct path
 or UserEditor won't start when using the Server gadgets!

 You should finally copy the docs (the one you are currently reading!) to
 the drawer @{fg fill}FAME:Documentation/@{fg text}, as this is the main storage place for
 all FAME related docs, but you could of course copy it to a different
 path and adjust the path to it in the UserEditor preferences!

 All the descibed steps are also supported by the @{b}Installerscript@{ub}, so it's 
 really recommended that you use it...

 That's all for installation, now have fun @{"using" LINK USAGE} the UserEditor!
@endnode

@REM ************************************************************************
@REM *                      STARTING OPTIONS                                *
@REM ************************************************************************

@node "START" "Startoptions from UserEditor"

                         @{u}How to start UserEditor@{uu}

UserEditor could be started in different ways:

 @{b}1@{ub}. Starting from WB via Double-Click on it's icon.

 @{b}2@{ub}. Starting from FAME-Server.
    
 @{b}3@{ub}. Starting from CLI (Template: BBS-LOCATION/A, USERNUM/N).


@{b}1. Starting from WB:@{ub}

Simply click on the Icon twice, UserEditor tries to load all required
Settings from the location where @{fg shine}FAME:@{fg text} points to.


@{b}2. Starting from FAME Server:@{ub}

You have two options starting UserEditor from the FAME Server: If you
only want to start UserEditor, use the Button '@{b}UserEditor@{ub}' found on
System Bank 1 of the FAME Server.

If you want to load automatically the Userdatas of a specific User,
which may also be currently online, then use the '@{b}UsEd@{ub}' button found
at the right side of the according node status line of the server.
Please check the FAME @{"Server Documentation" LINK FAME:Documentation/server.guide/MAIN_WINDOW} for further details about
these buttons.


@{b}3. Starting from CLI:@{ub}

When you start it from CLI, you have two possible Arguments to pass
through UserEditor when starting. Note that none of them is required
anymore (previous Versions required it!) to start UserEditor, just
if you wish to have some control over the behavour, you may use the
following Syntax:

                 @{fg shine}UserEditor <BBS-LOCATION/A> <USERNUM/N>@{fg text}

If you won't pass any arguments, UserEditor uses as FAME Location
the @{fg shine}FAME:@{fg text} Assign (this is normally @{b}REQUIRED@{ub} for FAME to work) and
will always load in the first user, known as the SysOp ;)

You may call it like this:

                          @{fg shine}UserEditor FAME_BETA:@{fg text}

...will use the FAME System found under the Assign @{fg shine}FAME_BETA:@{fg text} for all 
required datas to load.


Another possible call is: 
                           @{fg shine}UserEditor FAME: 213@{fg text}

...will use the FAME System found under the Assign @{fg shine}FAME:@{fg text} and after opening
the main window, will also load in the User found under Slot @{fg shine}213@{fg text}.

You don't have to specify the <USERNUM> argument, but if given, UserEditor
loads in the specified User after the main window is open. The same call 
did also the FAME-Server when starting the UserEditor from the Gadget @{b}UsEd@{ub}
(behind the Info-Gadget). See also the @{"Server Documentation" LINK FAME:Documentation/server.guide/MAIN_WINDOW} for further
infos about the UserEditor gadgets of the Server.
@endnode

@REM ************************************************************************
@REM *                          GENERAL USAGE                               *
@REM ************************************************************************

@node "USAGE" "Usage of UserEditor"

                           @{u}Usage of UserEditor@{uu}

@{u}General Informations:@{uu}

- Whenever you change anything from the actual user settings, UserEditor 
  keeps track of it and informs you when you are trying to load in other 
  settings. You have of course the possibility to save before proceeding.

- Every GUI element inside UserEditor has the @{b}MUI Bubble Help@{ub} feature and
  also a more detailed help inside this manual you are currently reading.
  Simply move the mouse over the element you wish to have more informations
  and press the '@{b}HELP@{ub}' key. UserEditor loads in the Guide file you have 
  defined in the @{"Preferences" LINK PREFS_HELPPATH} and pops up the according page where you find
  additional informations. 

- Many informations inside this manual are not very detailed, as most of
  these infos are already described in the @{"FAME.guide" LINK "FAME:Documentation/FAME.GUIDE/MAIN"}, so please take a
  look to this database to get more detailed informations !

- In the current Version (V1.30) it's @{b}not possible to edit users@{ub}, which are
  @{b}currently online in your system@{ub} !! Whenever you load in an user which is
  currently online, UserEditor informs you about this and it's up to you
  to decide if your changings should be lost....the complete Online Editing
  will be working only with the soon comming FAME @{b}V2.x@{ub} Versions, as the
  FAMEToolPort is now finished in this new Versions of FAME and it will be
  used by UserEditor to perform the communication with FAME.
  It's of course possible to deactivate the warning, but always keep the
  above text in mind !

- If you set a @{"Preset" LINK MAIN_BTN_PRESETS} to an user, please notice that only the fields 
  displayed in the Preset selection window will be changed in the
  user.datas, nothing more !


         @{"Click here to show an overview of all available Helptexts" LINK INDEX}
@endnode

