@REM ************************************************************************
@REM *                      MAIN WINDOW BUTTONS                             *
@REM ************************************************************************

@node "MAIN_BTN_LOAD" "BUTTON: Load - MENU: Project/Load..."

                             @{u}BUTTON: Load User@{uu}

                           @{u}MENU: Project/Load...@{uu}

When selected, UserEditor first checks out if you've changed current user
settings. If you did, UserEditor asks you if you want to loose current
changings. Answering NO brings you back to the main window. If you proceed,
UserEditor will open a Window containing a ListView Gadget with a sorted 
list of all your users, including inactive/deleted users.

UserEditor jumps automatically to the position in the List according to the
current username and activate the Listview-Cursor on it. Now you could choose
which user should be loaded by using the CRSR-Keys and Enter to select or by 
simply using the Mouse, or by pressing the Button @{b}LOAD@{ub}..:) You could abort 
this action by pressing the @{b}ABORT@{ub} Button or the Close Gadget. 

(ESC also closes the Window, that works with any MUI-Window!).

Since V0.44 it's also possible to change the sorting criteria of the User-
list. Simply click on the cycle gadget '@{fg shine}Sort by:@{fg text}' and the List will be sorted
either by names or by slotnumbers.

After selecting an user UserEditor loads in the specific datas and closes the
Listview-Window.
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BTN_SAVE" "BUTTON: Save - MENU: Project/Save User"

                             @{u}BUTTON: Save User@{uu}

                          @{u}MENU: Project/Save User@{uu}

When selected, UserEditor saves the current user datas to your user.data and
user.keys .

Nothing more to say about it I think..:)
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BTN_REACTIVATE" "BUTTON: Re-Active"

                             @{u}BUTTON: Re-Active@{uu}

This Button sets the current user-status to @{b}Validated@{ub}. If you have a new user,
you could validate him (give him access) by pressing this button. But you have
to set all other settings for yourself, i.e. the accesslevel, online time
etc.

If this is too many work for you, try the @{"Presets" link "MAIN_BTN_PRESETS" 0} Button, which makes all
settings automatically for you.

See also: @{"Inactive" link "MAIN_BTN_INACTIVE" 0}, @{"New User" link "MAIN_BTN_NEWUSER" 0}, @{"Delete" link "MAIN_BTN_DELETE" 0}
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BTN_INACTIVE" "BUTTON: Inactive"

                             @{u}BUTTON: Inactive@{uu}

This button switches current User's Status to @{b}Inactive@{ub}. In this State, the
user-entry remains in your user.datas, but the User itself is not able to get
into your BBS. Good for users, which are i.e. some weeks on holidays, and
don't want to get hacked...

See also: @{"Re-Activate" link "MAIN_BTN_REACTIVATE" 0}, @{"New User" link "MAIN_BTN_NEWUSER" 0}, @{"Delete" link "MAIN_BTN_DELETE" 0}
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BTN_NEWUSER" "BUTTON: New User"

                             @{u}BUTTON: New User@{uu}

With this button you could set the current user as @{b}New User@{ub}. In this state,
you have to @{"validate" link "MAIN_BTN_REACTIVATE" 0} the user, otherwise he's not able to do something in your
BBS.

See also: @{"Re-Activate" link "MAIN_BTN_REACTIVATE" 0}, @{"Delete" link "MAIN_BTN_DELETE" 0}, @{"Inactive" link "MAIN_BTN_INACTIVE" 0}
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BTN_DELETE" "BUTTON: Delete"

                              @{u}BUTTON: Delete@{uu}

By pressing this button, you set the current user status to @{b}Deleted@{ub}. In this
state, the next New User which comes into the BBS overrides the deleted
account before new user datas were append to your user.data. So it's sure
that you only have active or Inactive users in your user.data, not deleted
ones too.

See also: @{"Re-Activate" link "MAIN_BTN_REACTIVATE" 0}, @{"Inactive" link "MAIN_BTN_INACTIVE" 0}, @{"New User" link "MAIN_BTN_NEWUSER" 0}
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BTN_PRESETS" "BUTTON: Presets - MENU: Project/Set Preset"

                              @{u}BUTTON: Presets@{uu}

                         @{u}MENU: Project/Set Preset@{uu}

When you want to validate a user but also set all needed things for the
validated account automatically, you could use this Preset-Option. When
pressed, a new Window appears which shows you the first preset. Here you see
the following things:
@{fg shine}
ConfAlias, AccessLevel, Ratio, RatioType, UserFileBase, daily bytes/files@{fg text} and
@{fg shine}time limit.
@{fg text}
This are the fields in the user.data, which were set by the preset option. You
could choose the desired Preset by clicking on the CycleGadget @{b}PRESET@{ub}. 
FAME allows you to have a maximum of @{b}10@{ub} different presets including one 
Preset for NewUser settings which are configurable via 
@{fg fill}SystemEditor/Access/Presets@{fg text}.

Select the Preset you need and press the button @{b}Set to User@{ub}. This sets all
fields to the values you've seen in the Preset-Window. To abort press the
CloseGadget of the Window or the Cancel button.

@{u}NOTE:@{uu} Don't forget to save the current user-settings when using the Preset-
      option!!! Else you loose the settings.
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BTN_ENTRYUSER" "BUTTON: Entry User - MENU: User/Entry User"

                            @{u}BUTTON: Entry User@{uu}

                           @{u}MENU: User/Entry User@{uu}

                               @{i}New for V0.44@{ui}

This function allows to append an empty newuser to your user.datas. 

UserEditor first asks you if you really want to add a new user to your
user.datas. After proceeding, UserEditor first checks your user.data if 
a deleted user could be found. If any deleted user could be found, his old
account datas will be deleted and replaced by the default settings FAME has
defined for new users. If no deleted user is present in your user.datas, a 
new entry will be added to your user.datas/user.keys with empty account 
datas. Before you could change any of the new user settings, UserEditor 
adds now for all your conferences the new user datas to the conference's 
@{i}UserCnf.data@{ui} files. When everything is finished, simply enter the rest of 
the account datas for the new created user and save it again to make the 
changings permanent.
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BTN_CONFACC" "BUTTON: Conf. Acc. - MENU: User/Conf. Access"

                            @{u}BUTTON: Conf. Acc.@{uu}

                          @{u}MENU: User/Conf. Access@{uu}

This opens a new window which contains the conference depending user.datas
of the current user. Please look in Chapter @{"Conference Accounting" LINK CONF_ACCOUNTING} for
detailed informations about this options and take also a look to the FAME
docs to get more informations about the Conference Accounting Option of FAME.
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BTN_ADVSEARCH" "BUTTON: Adv. Search - MENU: User/Adv. Search"

                            @{u}BUTTON: Adv. Search@{uu}

                          @{u}MENU: User/Adv. Search@{uu}

                               @{i}New for V0.44@{ui}

This opens a new window which contains a more complex search function then
the @{"normal Searching by Name" LINK SEARCH_USER} function.

It's possible to search in the @{b}Ratio@{ub}, @{b}Level@{ub}, @{b}Conference Access@{ub} and @{b}Location@{ub}
fields of the user.datas at once. It supports also valid A-DOS Patterns to 
perform high-end searchings. ;) 

Just take a look to the section @{"Advanced Searching" LINK ADV_SEARCH} for more detailed 
informations.
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BTN_QUIT" "BUTTON: Quit UserEditor - MENU: Project/Quit UserEditor"

                         @{u}BUTTON: Quit UserEditor@{uu}

                      @{u}MENU: Project/Quit UserEditor@{uu}

Exit Program...what else..:) 

Depending on your Preferences settings, you may be asked if you really
wish to exit UserEditor. Look in chapter @{"Preferences" LINK PREFERENCES} for further 
instructions about UserEditor Preferences.
@endnode

@node "BTN_PREV" "BUTTON: Previous User - MENU: User/Previous User"

                           @{u}BUTTON: Previous User@{uu}

                         @{u}MENU: User/Previous User@{uu}

When pressing, UserEditor loads in the previous user. If you have made 
changings to current User settings, UserEditor asks you to confirm the 
loading or to save first the actual datas. When you reached the first 
user in your user.data, a small infotext appears in all Status/Username 
displays to inform you that you have reached the beginning.

See also: @{"Next" link "BTN_NEXT" 0}, @{"First/Last User" link "FIRST_LAST_USER" 0}, @{"Enter Slotnumber" LINK MAIN_ENTER_SLOT}
@endnode

@node "BTN_NEXT" "BUTTON: Next User - MENU: Next User"

                             @{u}BUTTON: Next User@{uu}

                              @{u}MENU: Next User@{uu}

When pressing, UserEditor loads in the next user. If you have made 
changings to current User settings, UserEditor asks you to confirm the 
loading or to save first the actual datas. When you reached the last user
in your user.data, a small infotext appears in all Status/Username displays 
to inform you that you have reached the end of the user.data.

See also: @{"Prev" link "BTN_PREV" 0}, @{"First/Last User" link "FIRST_LAST_USER" 0}, @{"Enter Slotnumber" LINK MAIN_ENTER_SLOT}
@endnode

@node "MAIN_ENTER_SLOT" "INPUT: Slotnumber"

                             @{u}INPUT: Slotnumber@{uu}

This field could be used to enter directly a slotnumber to load. UserEditor
checks first if you have altered any of the actual user settings, in this
case you will be informed about the changings and it's up to you to loose
them or to save first. Now UserEditor loads in the new slotnumber. If you
enter invalid values, UserEditor informs you about this and aborts, else
the given slotnumber will be loaded.

See also: @{"Prev" link "BTN_PREV" 0}, @{"Next" link "BTN_NEXT" 0}, @{"First/Last User" link "FIRST_LAST_USER" 0}
@endnode

@REM ************************************************************************
@REM *                        MENU DESCRIPTIONS                             *
@REM ************************************************************************

@node "FIRST_LAST_USER" "MENU: User/First & Last User"

                       @{u}MENU: User/First & Last User@{uu}

With this two menu-entries you could jump directly to the beginning/end of
your user.data. This is useful if you have many users and want to view only
the last users etc. 

See also: @{"Prev" link "BTN_PREV" 0}, @{"Next" link "BTN_NEXT" 0}, @{"Enter Slotnumber" LINK MAIN_ENTER_SLOT}
@endnode

@node "SEARCH_USER" "MENU: User/Search User - BUTTON: Search User"

                          @{u}MENU: User/Search User@{uu}

                            @{u}BUTTON: Search User@{uu}

When selected a new window opens and you will be asked to enter a name or
a pattern to search for. If you have modified the actual settings, you will
be informed about this and it's up to you to decide if you wish to loose
the changings. Now enter the name of the user you wish to search for, also 
all AmigaDOS wildcards and patterns are allowed for usage. Invalid patterns 
will be filtered out and answered with an errormessage.

If you wish to abort, simply let the name field empty and UserEditor will
return to the main window or use the @{b}Abort@{ub} Button or the close gadget.

When you have entered a valid searchname/-pattern, UserEditor starts now
to scan your user.keys . This will be shown via a progress indicator. If
UserEditor finds any matching pattern, you will be informed that a
matching user has been found and you could now decide if this user should be
loaded and set as actual user. You may also continue the search without
loading the first matching user first.

If you have loaded the matching user and  you wish to continue the 
searching, simply call again the Search User option, UserEditor will
then ask you if you wish to continue the searching from the current user 
or if you wish to start from the beginning of your user.datas.

If no matching pattern could be found, UserEditor informs you about this
and return back to the main window.

Since V0.44 there exists an additional searching algorithmus inside User-
Editor called @{b}Advanced Searching@{ub}, which allows a more complex searching
inside your user.datas. Just check out the Chapter @{"Advanced Searching" LINK ADV_SEARCH}
for detailed informations about this new function.
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BTN_NEWSCAN" "MENU: User/New User Scan - BUTTON: New User Scan"

                         @{u}MENU: User/New User Scan@{uu}

                           @{u}BUTTON: New User Scan@{uu}

This option allows you to scan your user.datas for any new users. If 
UserEditor found a new user, it will load it's datas and set him as
actual user. Don't forget to save the settings if you set a new user
to @{"validated" LINK MAIN_BTN_REACTIVATE} state!
@endnode

@node "SWITCH_MAIN_PAGES" "MENU: Pages/Page 1..6"

                           @{u}MENU: Pages/Page 1..6@{uu}

These six entries allows to quickly change the main window pages. The 
numbers are from left to right, so the @{"main settings" LINK MAIN_PAGE1} page has number @{b}1@{ub},
the @{"byte & file" LINK MAIN_PAGE2} settings Page @{b}2@{ub} etc...
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BTN_PREFS" "MENU: Configuration/Preferences"

                      @{u}MENU: Configuration/Preferences@{uu}

This opens the Preferences Window to configure UserEditor. Please look in
chapter UserEditor @{"Preferences" LINK PREFERENCES} for detailed informations about the prefs.
@endnode

@node "MUI_PREFS" "MENU: Configuration/MUI Preferences"

                    @{u}MENU: Configuration/MUI Preferences@{uu}

This option starts the MUI Configprogram for UserEditor. Useful if you have
disabled all additional MUI Window-Gadgets and would like to re-configure
the MUI Settings of UserEditor.
@endnode

@node "ABOUT" "MENU: Project/About"

                      @{u}MENU: Project/About UserEditor@{uu}

Shows the wellknown about requester. Also some informations about the
installed BBS System will be printed, like SysOp, BBSName and amount of
active nodes.
@endnode

@node "ABOUT_MUI" "MENU: Project/About MUI"

                          @{u}MENU: Project/About MUI@{uu}

This open MUI's internal About class to show the versionnumbers of the
installed MUI Version.
@endnode

@REM ************************************************************************
@REM *                       MAIN WINDOW PAGES                              *
@REM ************************************************************************

@node "MAIN_PAGE1" "MAIN WINDOW: Main Settings (Page 1)"

                               @{u}Main Settings@{uu}

On this page the main settings of the actual users are displayed. The
following fields are available here:

@{b}Username@{ub}     - The name of the current user. This is the global username.

@{b}Password@{ub}     - The password of the user. For more security, this password
               will be hidden with dots.

@{b}Location@{ub}     - Normally the group of the user.

@{b}City@{ub}         - From where the user calls (City/Country).

@{b}Phone@{ub}        - The Phonenumber of the user.

@{b}Birthday@{ub}     - The birthday of the user in USA Dateformat (MM-DD-YY).

@{b}Level@{ub}        - Accesslevel of the current user.

@{b}Calls@{ub}        - Amount of calls for the current user.

@{b}Time Limit@{ub}   - User's time limit in seconds.

@{b}Time Used@{ub}    - Time used today for the current user (in seconds).

@{b}Msg Write@{ub}    - Global amount of messages written by the user.

@{b}Msg Read@{ub}     - Global amount of messages readen by the user.


                 @{fg shine}Also the following buttons are available:@{fg text}

             @{"ConfAcc." LINK MAIN_BTN_CONFACC}, @{"User search" LINK SEARCH_USER}, @{"Adv. Search" LINK MAIN_BTN_ADVSEARCH}, @{"NewUser Scan" LINK MAIN_BTN_NEWSCAN}

               @{fg shine}And these buttons are available on all pages:@{fg text}

@{"Load" LINK MAIN_BTN_LOAD}, @{"Save" LINK MAIN_BTN_SAVE}, @{"Delete" LINK MAIN_BTN_DELETE}, @{"Reactive" LINK MAIN_BTN_REACTIVATE}, @{"Inactive" LINK MAIN_BTN_INACTIVE}, @{"NewUser" LINK MAIN_BTN_NEWUSER}, @{"Presets" LINK MAIN_BTN_PRESETS}, @{"Entry User" LINK MAIN_BTN_ENTRYUSER}, @{"Quit" LINK MAIN_BTN_QUIT}
@endnode

@node "MAIN_PAGE2" "MAIN WINDOW: Byte & File Settings (Page 2)"

                           @{u}Byte & File Settings@{uu}

This Page contains global Byte/File settings for the current user. The
following fields are available here:

@{b}Uploads@{ub}          - Global amount of files uploaded.

@{b}Downloads@{ub}        - Global amount of files downloaded.

@{b}Bytes Uploaded@{ub}   - Global amount of bytes uploaded.

@{b}Bytes Downloaded@{ub} - Global amount of bytes downloaded.

@{b}File Limit@{ub}       - Global amount of files allowed to download.

@{b}Byte Limit@{ub}       - Global amount of bytes allowed to download.

@{b}Files nuked@{ub}      - Global amount of files nuked.

@{b}Bytes nuked@{ub}      - Global amount of bytes nuked.

@{b}File Bonus@{ub}       - Global amount of files added to every upload as Bonus.

@{b}Byte Bonus@{ub}       - Global amount of bytes added to every upload as Bonus.

@{b}DailyDLBytes@{ub}     - Global amount of bytes allowed to download per day.

@{b}DailyDLFiles@{ub}     - Global amount of files allowed to download per day.

@{b}Ratio@{ub}            - Defines the type of ratio the user has. 0 = disabled,
                   any other value defines the ratio as x : 1, means that
                   the user is able to download x times more than he has
                   uploaded to your System. The calculation and what kind
                   of check FAME should make for the ratio depends on the
                   RatioType setting (see below).
                   
@{b}RatioType@{ub}        - Defines the Ratiotype, possible values are: Bytes, Files
                   and Bytes & files combined. If the user has a ratio of 0,
                   this field will be ignored, as it is useless if the user
                   has a disabled account.

@{b}Conf Alias@{ub}       - Defines the conference alias, which describes for which
                   conferences the actual user has access to. The datafiles
                   required for this will be created in the SystemEditor
                   under SysEd->Access->Conference Access. To change this
                   value, you may either enter the conference alias by
                   yourself (without the extension .dat!), or use the popup
                   button and choose the desired Alias via an ASL requester.
@endnode

@node "MAIN_PAGE3" "MAIN WINDOW: User Flags (Page 3)"

                                @{u}User Flags@{uu}

This page allows to set various flags for the current user. Most of them
will be set by the user himself, as they reflect his personal configuration 
inside FAME. Also some flags are included which aren't setable by the user !

The following flags are available on this page:

@{b}Expert@{ub}             - If set, user won't get the menu(x).txt files after the
                     execution of a command. This is called Expert Mode.

@{b}Msg CLS@{ub}            - If set, FAME clears the screen after a message, this 
                     increases output speed (less scrolling).

@{b}File CLS@{ub}           - If set, FAME clears the screen after every shown file-
                     listing. This increases output speed (less scrolling).

@{b}Pause Screen@{ub}       - If set, FAME wait for a keypress after showing a complete
                     page of text. 

@{b}ASCII Msg@{ub}          - If set, FAME's internal LineEditor won't show line-
                     numbers and also doesn't use them, so you may now able
                     to snap in ASCII pictures i.e. This option takes no
                     effect if the user is using the FullScreen Editor.

@{b}Hidden@{ub}             - If set, the user won't be shown in the WHO command
                     unless someone called WHO with the FORCE argument. 
                     Without this option, WHO will show an 'Awaiting Connect'
                     for the hidden node.

@{b}Spy User@{ub}           - If set, FAME will capture user's activities auto-
                     matically and stores the captures in the directory
                     FAME:Capture/<X>/<Y>, where <X> is the slotnumber of the
                     user and <Y> is the date of the capturing, <Y> is also 
                     the capture file (text). 
                          @{fg shine}THIS OPTION IS NOT CONFIGURABLE BY THE USER !@{fg text}
                     
@{b}UserFileBase@{ub}       - Currently not functional! This option will be used later
                     to allow users to have their own HD-Space inside your 
                     BBS, to store i.e. own Web pages or similar.
                          @{fg shine}THIS OPTION IS NOT CONFIGURABLE BY THE USER !@{fg text}

@{b}Msg Rooming@{ub}        - Another setable feature of the lineeditor. If set, the
                     lineeditor provides automatic insertion, which means
                     that the editor will put the cursor after a linefeed
                     to the same row the cursor was in the previous line,
                     allowing you to create easily tables or adverts ;)
                     This mode is also known as auto-indent mode.

@{b}String Edit@{ub}        - If set, this will enable additional edit functions like
                     using the cursor keys etc. 

@{b}Fast Logout@{ub}        - If set, FAME will simply hang up the line when the
                     user loggs out instead of showing any logoff texts.

@{b}Global UL@{ub}          - If set, global uploading is possible. Not implemented
                     yet, therefor Gadget won't work!

@{b}Global DL@{ub}          - If set, the user is able to download all files from all
                     conferences at once, without joining first the conf 
                     where he has files flagged. 

@{b}Global View@{ub}        - If set, global Viewing is enabled. This allows an user
                     to view a textfile by name from any conference without
                     joining the conference first where the textfile is
                     stored.

@{b}Global Zippy@{ub}       - If set, global Searching is enabled. This allows an
                     user to search for files inside all conferences. 

@{b}Auto Quote@{ub}         - If set, FAME will quote the whole original message to
                     the reply message. Useful if you use the FullEditor and
                     want to edit the whole message inside the FullEditor, 
                     which is much easier.

@{b}Keep private@{ub}       - If set, FAME will keep the public/private status of the
                     original message when replying to a mail. If not set,
                     the user will be asked for the status of the replied
                     mail.

@{b}Keep subject@{ub}       - If set, FAME will keep the subject of the original mail
                     when replying to a mail. If not set, the user is able
                     to edit the subject before replying.

@{b}Background Check@{ub}   - If set, FAME will check a file just after it recieves
                     it completly, regardeless if the user uploads more
                     files. This saves much time for the user.

@{b}Autoforce on WHO@{ub}   - If set, FAME will start the internal WHO in FORCE mode
                     to show also hidden users.

@{b}Background Posting@{ub} - If set, FAME will try to post a (already) checked file
                     to the upload dir. Only if the file contain no file_id
                     description it will be shown to the user who uploaded
                     it, else it will be posted to the dir in Background.
                     Saves much more time for the user ;)

@{b}Fixed Filenames@{ub}    - If set, FAME allows only 12 chars for filenames (for
                     the MS-Dos compatibility, pfft...). If not set FAME
                     allows 30 chars for filenames (Amiga Standard !!),
                     except the conferences where the sysop has defined
                     12 chars as maximum.

@{b}UNUSED24@{ub}           - 

@{b}UNUSED25@{ub}           -
@endnode

@node "MAIN_PAGE4" "MAIN WINDOW: More UserFlags (Page 4)"

                              @{u}More UserFlags@{uu}

                       This flags are not used yet.

@{b}UNUSED26@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED27@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED28@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED29@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED30@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED31@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED32@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED33@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED34@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED35@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED36@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED37@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED38@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED39@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED40@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED41@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED42@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED43@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED44@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED45@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED46@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED47@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED48@{ub} -

@{b}UNUSED49@{ub} -
@endnode

@node "MAIN_PAGE5" "MAIN WINDOW: User Options (Page 5)"

                               @{u}User Options@{uu}

This page contains additional user options. Some of them are disabled because
they are currently not implemented in FAME.

@{b}Editor@{ub}         - Defines the Editortype used by the user. Possible values are
                 LineEditor, FullEditor, Other Editor, Ask For Editor.

@{b}ANSI@{ub}           - Defines user's ANSI Flag. Possible values are: on, off, Ask.

@{b}Scan@{ub}           - Defines the Confscanning for the user. Possible values are:
                 Mails only, Files only, Files & Mail,Ask, None.

@{b}FileID.DIZ@{ub}     - Defines the FileID.diz extraction for files. Possible values
                 are: Ask, Auto, Off.

@{b}CryptMessagePW@{ub} - Not implemented yet in FAME.

@{b}UserFileBasePW@{ub} - Not implemented yet in FAME.

@{b}Mail Crypt@{ub}     - Not implemented yet in FAME.

@{b}Computer@{ub}       - Shows the computertype of the actual user.

@{b}Modem@{ub}          - Shows the modemtype of the actual user.
@endnode

@node "MAIN_PAGE6" "MAIN WINDOW: Misc. Options (Page 6)"

                               @{u}Misc. Options@{uu}

Here are now the missing options which had no room on the other pages ;)

@{b}Relogins@{ub}      - Amount of allowed relogins per day.

@{b}Pages@{ub}         - Amount of SysOp pages.

@{b}Chats@{ub}         - Amount of SysOp chats.

@{b}LineLen@{ub}       - User's line length.

@{b}All Hacks@{ub}     - Amount of password hackings.

@{b}Last Baud@{ub}     - Last connected Baudrate.

@{b}ConfReJoin@{ub}    - Number of conference the user will autorejoin after a login.
                If set to 0, the last conference of the user will be used
                as autorejoin (see below).

@{b}Last Conf@{ub}     - Number of conference the user was joined before logging out.

@{b}ShellNumLines@{ub} - Amount of Lines to be used in Shellmode.

@{b}Min UL@{ub}        - Minimum Upload CPS rate.

@{b}Max UL@{ub}        - Maximum Upload CPS rate.

@{b}Min DL@{ub}        - Minimum Download CPS rate.

@{b}Max DL@{ub}        - Maximum Download CPS rate.

@{b}First@{ub}         - This is the first date the user joined your BBS. Also known
                as the account date, as it reflects the time when the user
                was written first to the user.datas.

@{b}Last@{ub}          - Time of last login. 
@endnode

@REM ************************************************************************
@REM *                     CONFERENCE ACCOUNTING                            *
@REM ************************************************************************

@node CONF_ACCOUNTING "Some informations about Conference Accounting"

                   @{u}Conference Accounting - Informations@{uu}

The conference accounting allows sysops to have conference specific user
settings. This means that the global user.datas are only valid for fields
not affected by conf accounting. Most of the datas are configurable for
every conference, so it's possible to give an user a disabled ratio in
conference @{b}1@{ub} but an ratio of @{b}3:1@{ub} for conference 2 i.e. To use this feature
you have to set the Ratio type from Global to the state you wish to use.
See @{"RatioType" LINK CONF_RATIOTYPE} for detailed infos about this cycle gadget. If Ratiotype is
set to @{b}GLOBAL@{ub}, the user has for all conferences the same settings, so the
user.data file is only important. If you have set the Ratiotype to any other
setting except GLOBAL, you could now setup user settings for all your 
conferences seperatly. 

See @{"FAME.guide" LINK "FAME:DOCUMENTATION/FAME.GUIDE/MAIN"} for further informations. 

Please remember that UserEditor controls all your conferences with their
real conference numbers, relative Conference-Numbers won't shown here as
they will too much confusing and give too much overhead to UserEditor.

UserEditor allows to edit/view almost all entries the internal UserEditor
of FAME also supports. Click on the gadgets below to get more informations:

                                  @{b}@{u}Buttons:@{ub}@{uu}

			@{"         <-- Prev          " LINK CONF_BTN_PREV}
			@{"         Next -->          " LINK CONF_BTN_NEXT}
			@{"           Save            " LINK CONF_BTN_SAVE}	
			@{"        Change Conf.       " LINK CONF_BTN_CHANGE}
			@{"           Quit            " LINK CONF_BTN_QUIT}
			@{"       Conf Number         " LINK CONF_NUMBER}

                                   @{b}@{u}Pages:@{ub}@{uu}

			@{"Main User Settings.(Page 1)" LINK CONF_PAGE_1}
			@{"Byte/File settings.(Page 2)" LINK CONF_PAGE_2}
			@{"User Options.......(Page 3)" LINK CONF_PAGE_3}
			@{"Other User Options.(Page 4)" LINK CONF_PAGE_4}

                                   @{b}@{u}Other:@{ub}@{uu}

			@{"        Ratio/-Type        " LINK CONF_RATIOTYPE}
@endnode

@ REM ***********************************************************************
@ REM *                 CONFERENCE ACCOUNTING - BUTTONS                     *
@ REM ***********************************************************************

@node "CONF_BTN_PREV" "CONFERENCE ACCOUNTING BUTTON: <-- Prev. (Previous Conference)"

                             @{u}BUTTON: <-- Prev.@{uu}

                      @{i}(Conference accounting window)@{ui}


This button loads in the previous conference. If you have reached the first
conference available on your system, a DisplayBeep() will be performed and
UserEditor stops.

If you have made any changings to current user conference settings and 
try to load in a previous conference, UserEditor informs you that you are
about to loose the current changings etc...
@endnode

@node CONF_BTN_NEXT "CONFERENCE ACCOUNTING BUTTON: Next --> (Next Conference)"

                             @{u}BUTTON: Next -->@{uu}

                      @{i}(Conference accounting window)@{ui}


This button loads in the next conference. If you have reached the last
available conference from your system a DisplayBeep() will be performed
and UserEditor stops.

If you have made any changings to current user conference settings and 
try to load in the next conference, UserEditor informs you that you are
about to loose the current changings etc...
@endnode

@node CONF_BTN_SAVE "CONFERENCE ACCOUNTING BUTTON: Save"

                               @{u}BUTTON: Save@{uu}

                      @{i}(Conference accounting window)@{ui}


Click on this button to save the current conference datas to disk. 
@endnode

@node CONF_BTN_CHANGE "CONFERENCE ACCOUNTING BUTTON: Change Conference"

                           @{u}BUTTON: Change Conf.@{uu}

                      @{i}(Conference accounting window)@{ui}


This button allows you to load in specific conference datas. A list of all
available conferences will appear and you could now choose which conference
you wish to load. If you have made any changings to the current settings
and load in another conference, you will be prompted if you wish to loose
current changings etc.

Select @{b}Abort@{ub} if you won't load another conference.
@endnode

@node CONF_BTN_QUIT "CONFERENCE ACCOUNTING BUTTON: Quit"

                               @{u}BUTTON: Quit@{uu}

                      @{i}(Conference accounting window)@{ui}


Click here to cancel the conference accounting settings. The window will be
closed and you will return back to the main menu.

If you have made any changings to current user conference settings and 
click on the QUIT button, UserEditor informs you that you are about to 
loose the current changings etc...
@endnode

@node CONF_NUMBER "CONFERENCE ACCOUNTING INTEGER: Conference Number"

                        @{u}INTEGER: Conference Number@{uu}

                      @{i}(Conference accounting window)@{ui}


This gadget allows you to jump to a particular conference by entering here
the according conference number (the REAL conference number, *NOT* the
relative one!!!). If you have entered a valid conference number, UserEditor
loads in the according conference datas.

If you have made any changings to current user conference settings and 
click on the QUIT button, UserEditor informs you that you are about to 
loose the current changings etc...
@endnode

@node CONF_PAGE_1 "CONFERENCE ACCOUNTING: User Settings (Page 1)"

                       @{u}PAGE: User Settings (Page 1)@{uu}

                      @{i}(Conference accounting window)@{ui}


This page contains the important user settings for the current conference:

@{b}Conf. Username@{ub} - The name of the user in the current conference.

@{b}Sentby@{ub}         - The SentBy line for the current conference.

@{b}Msg Write@{ub}      - Amount of messages written in the current conference.

@{b}Msg scanned@{ub}    - Amount of messages scanned in the current conference.

@{b}Time Limit@{ub}     - Time limit per day in seconds.

@{b}Msg Read@{ub}       - Amount of messages read in the current conference.

@{b}EALL's read@{ub}    - Amount of EALL's read in the current conference.

@{b}Time Used@{ub}      - Time used today in seconds.

@{b}# of joins@{ub}     - Amount of joinings to the current conference.

@{b}PW Hacks@{ub}       - Amount of password hackings for the current conference.

@{b}Time total@{ub}     - Time total available for the current conference.
@endnode

@node CONF_PAGE_2 "CONFERENCE ACCOUNTING: Bytes (Page 2)"

                           @{u}PAGE: Bytes (Page 2)@{uu}

                      @{i}(Conference accounting window)@{ui}


This page contains all User Byte/File settings for the current conference:

@{b}Uploads@{ub}      - Amount of files uploaded.

@{b}Bytes UL@{ub}     - Amount of bytes uploaded.

@{b}ByteLimit@{ub}    - Byte limit.

@{b}FileBonus@{ub}    - Additional file bonus for an upload.

@{b}Downloads@{ub}    - Amount of files downloaded.

@{b}Bytes DL@{ub}     - Amount of bytes downloaded.

@{b}FileLimit@{ub}    - File limit.

@{b}Dai.BytesDL@{ub}  - Amount of bytes allowed to download per day (0 = no limit).

@{b}Bytes nuked@{ub}  - Amount of bytes nuked.

@{b}Files nuked@{ub}  - Amount of files nuked.

@{b}Byte Bonus@{ub}   - Additional byte bonus for an upload.

@{b}Dai.FilesDL@{ub}  - Amount of files allowed to download per day (0 = no limit).
@endnode

@node CONF_PAGE_3 "CONFERENCE ACCOUNTING: Options (Page 3)"

                          @{u}PAGE: Options (Page 3)@{uu}

                      @{i}(Conference accounting window)@{ui}


This page contains conference-specific options:

@{b}Scan for new messages@{ub} - If set, FAME scans this conference for new messages.

@{b}Use conference datas@{ub}  - If set, FAME uses the conf. user.data, else the
                        global user.datas will be used.

@{b}Scan for new files@{ub}    - If set, FAME scans this conference for new files.

@{b}Conf. Access@{ub}          - This flag could be set by the user to indicate if
                        he wish to see the current conference or let FAME
                        hide it.

@{b}Use Zooming@{ub}           - If set, FAME will use Zooming for the messages.
                        @{fg shine}(NOT IMPLEMENTED YET!)@{fg text}

@{b}UNUSED 07@{ub}             - 

@{b}UNUSED 08@{ub}             - 

@{b}UNUSED 09@{ub}             - 

@{b}UNUSED 10@{ub}             - 

@{b}UNUSED 11@{ub}             - 

@{b}UNUSED 12@{ub}             - 

@{b}UNUSED 13@{ub}             - 
@endnode

@node CONF_PAGE_4 "CONFERENCE ACCOUNTING: Misc. (Page 4)"

                           @{u}PAGE: Misc. (Page 4)@{uu}

                      @{i}(Conference accounting window)@{ui}


This page contains miscellaneous settings for the current conference:

@{b}Min UL CPS@{ub}  - Lowest CPS rate for uploading.

@{b}Max UL CPS@{ub}  - Highest CPS rate for uploading.

@{b}Min DL CPS@{ub}  - Lowest CPS rate for downloading.

@{b}Max DL CPS@{ub}  - Highest CPS rate for downloading.

@{b}First Date@{ub}  - Date of first visiting the actual conference.

@{b}Last Date@{ub}   - Date of last visit of the actual conference.
@endnode

@node CONF_RATIOTYPE "CONFERENCE ACCOUNTING : Ratio/-Type"

                             @{u}CYCLE: Ratiotype@{uu}

                      @{i}(Conference accounting window)@{ui}

Here you could set which type of ratio the user should have for the current
conference. The following values are possible:

@{b}Bytes@{ub}           - The Ratio depends on the uploaded/downloaded bytes.
 
@{b}Files@{ub}           - The Ratio depends on the uploaded/downloaded files.

@{b}Bytes & Files@{ub}   - The Ratio depends on both ul'ed/dl'ed bytes & files.

@{b}Global@{ub}          - No conference specific ratio, use the ratio from the
                   global user.data settings.

@{u}NOTE:@{uu} If you set @{i}GLOBAL@{ui} to @{i}ALL@{ui} conference datas, the conference accounting
      is @{u}DISABLED@{uu} for the actual user!


                              @{u}INTEGER: Ratio@{uu}

This sets the ratio for the actual user. A ratio of @{b}0@{ub} means disabled. If
you have i.e. setup the Ratiotype to @{i}BYTES@{ui} and a Ratio of @{i}3@{ui}, so the actual
user have to upload @{i}100kb@{ui} to be able to download @{i}300kb@{ui}.
@endnode

@REM *********************************************************************
@REM ***                   UserEditor PREFERENCES                     ***
@REM *********************************************************************

@node "PREFERENCES" "WINDOW: UserEditor Preferences"

                            @{u}WINDOW: Preferences@{uu}

Here you can specify the preferences of UserEditor. The Prefs will be saved
in the Programdirectory of UserEditor under the Name '@{fg shine}UserEditor.prefs@{fg text}'.

Here's a brief description of all GUI elements found inside the Prefs Window:

                           @{b}Preferences-Settings:@{ub}

                         @{"     Online Help Path    " LINK PREFS_HELPPATH}	
                         @{"Exit without Confirmation" LINK PREFS_FASTEXIT}
                         @{"  Warn for online users  " LINK PREFS_WARNONLINE}

                                 @{b}Buttons:@{ub}

	                 @{"     Load Preferences    " LINK PREFS_LOAD}	
                         @{"     Save Preferences    " LINK PREFS_SAVE}
                         @{"      Use Preferences    " LINK PREFS_USE}	
                         @{"   Cancel Preferences    " LINK PREFS_CANCEL}

@endnode

@node "PREFS_HELPPATH" "PREFERENCES - STRING: Online Help Path"

                         @{u}STRING: Online Help Path@{uu}

                           @{i}(Preferences Window)@{ui}


Here you define the path and filename to the @{AMIGAGUIDE} file you are 
currently reading. This allows to have context-sensitive online help simply
by moving the mouse over any gadget of UserEditor and pressing the '@{fg shine}HELP@{fg text}' 
key. This will pop the Guide and load in the according chapter to give
you more help about the selected gadget.
@endnode

@node "PREFS_FASTEXIT" "PREFERENCES - CHECKMARK: Exit without Confirmation"

                   @{u}CHECKMARK: Exit without Confirmation@{uu}

                           @{i}(Preferences Window)@{ui}


Normally if you leave UserEditor, you will be prompted if you really want
to exit now. If you don't like the Exit confirmation, you could switch it
off by setting this checkmark. When selected UserEditor will exit silently.
@endnode

@node "PREFS_WARNONLINE" "PREFERENCES - CHECKMARK: Warn for online Users"

                      @{u}CHECKMARK: Warn for Online User@{uu}

                           @{i}(Preferences Window)@{ui}

If you don't wish to see a warning requester whenever you load-in an user
which is currently online, simply disable this checkmark, but you have
to check yourself, if the user you are currently editing is online or not. 
Read @{"HERE" LINK "USAGE"} for further details why it's so important to check for online users!
@endnode

@node "PREFS_LOAD" "PREFERENCES - BUTTON: Load"

                               @{u}BUTTON: Load@{uu}

                           @{i}(Preferences Window)@{ui}


Loads in already saved Preferences. Useful if you wish to restore the old
settings. If you have altered the preferences, you will be prompted if you
really want to loose current settings and reload the old one.
@endnode

@node "PREFS_SAVE" "PREFERENCES - BUTTON: Save"

                               @{u}BUTTON: Save@{uu}

                           @{i}(Preferences Window)@{ui}


Saves the current preferences as file '@{fg shine}PROGDIR:UserEditor.prefs@{fg text}' and closes
the preferences window.
@endnode

@node "PREFS_USE" "PREFERENCES - BUTTON: Use"

                                @{u}BUTTON: Use@{uu}

                           @{i}(Preferences Window)@{ui}


Uses the actual preferences settings but doesn't save them to disk. Useful
to test different configurations before saving them finally.
@endnode

@node "PREFS_CANCEL" "PREFERENCES - BUTTON: Cancel"

                              @{u}BUTTON: Cancel@{uu}

                           @{i}(Preferences Window)@{ui}


Aborts the preferences section and return back to main window. All changings
of the preferences are lost.
@endnode

@REM *********************************************************************
@REM ***                    ADVANCED SEARCH WINDOW                     ***
@REM *********************************************************************

@node "ADV_SEARCH" "WINDOW: Advanced Search Window"

                      @{u}WINDOW: Advanced Search Window@{uu}

Here you have the possibility to make a more complex searching inside your
user.datas. Adv. Searching supports all valid Amiga-DOS Patterns or complete
textmatching. You could choose which of the supported User.data fields should
be scanned, currently supported are the @{b}Level@{ub}, @{b}Ratio@{ub}, @{b}Location@{ub}, @{b}Conf. Access@{ub},
@{b}First login@{ub} and @{b}Last login@{ub} date fields. 

Whenever you start a search and any matching user could be found, it will be
immediatly added to the listview. After the searching is finished,
UserEditor writes down how much matchings are found. You may now select one
of the found entries from the Listview with a double click and it will be
loaded inside the Main Window. You could now edit this user or select another
user from the Listview. The Advanced Search Window will be closed only if you
press the @{b}Cancel@{ub} button, because it runs asynchronous to the main window to
allow the usage of both windows.

If you are running a low resolution, it may happen that you have problems
getting back the advanced Search window. In this case simply click again
on the Adv. Search button found on the main window and the Adv. Search win
will pop to front immediatly.

          @{u}@{b}The following Gadgets are available inside this window:@{uu}@{ub}

			   @{"  Search Pattern   " LINK ADV_PATTERN}
			   @{"  Search Location  " LINK ADV_LOCATION}
			   @{"Search  Conf. Alias" LINK ADV_CONFACCESS}
			   @{"    Search Ratio   " LINK ADV_RATIO}
			   @{"  Search Userlevel " LINK ADV_LEVEL}
			   @{"Search First Login " LINK ADV_FIRSTLOGIN}
			   @{" Search Last Login " LINK ADV_LASTLOGIN}
			   @{"    The Listview   " LINK ADV_LV}
			   @{"    Start Search   " LINK ADV_START}
			   @{" Abort Adv. Search " LINK ADV_STOP}

                Select the chapter from which you require 
                 more informations or click @{"HERE" LINK INDEX} for Index
@endnode

@node "ADV_PATTERN" "ADVANCED SEARCHING - STRING: SearchPattern/-String"

                       @{u}STRING: SearchPattern/-String@{uu}

                         @{i}(Advanced Search Window)@{ui}


Here you must enter the string or pattern to search for. A maximum of 128
chars is allowed, and you may use every valid Amiga-DOS Pattern that you
require, i.e.:
                         @{fg shine}(#?trsi#?|#?fame#?)@{fg text}

Will search in the given fields for any matching either with "@{fg shine}TRSI@{fg text}" @{b}OR@{ub} "@{fg shine}FAME@{fg text}".

Please notice that the searching is @{b}case-insensitive@{ub} for better performance.
If you don't enter any searchstring and try to start the searching, 
UserEditor stops with an errormessage and reactivates the textentry field.
@endnode

@node "ADV_LOCATION" "ADVANCED SEARCHING - CHECKMARK: Group/Location"

                         @{u}CHECKMARK: Group/Location@{uu}

                         @{i}(Advanced Search Window)@{ui}


Select this checkmark if you wish to search inside the @{b}Group/Location@{ub} field
of the FAME user.datas.

You have to specify at least one searching field to start the searching!

@{b}SEE ALSO:@{ub} @{"Ratio" LINK ADV_RATIO}, @{"UserLevel" LINK ADV_LEVEL}, @{"Conference Alias" LINK ADV_CONFACCESS}, @{"First Login" LINK ADV_FIRSTLOGIN}, @{"Last Login" LINK ADV_LASTLOGIN}
@endnode

@node "ADV_CONFACCESS" "ADVANCED SEARCHING - CHECKMARK: Conference Alias"

                          @{u}CHECKMARK: Conf. Alias@{uu}

                         @{i}(Advanced Search Window)@{ui}


Select this checkmark if you wish to search inside the @{b}Conference Alias@{ub}
field of the FAME user.datas.

You have to specify at least one searching field to start the searching!

@{b}SEE ALSO:@{ub} @{"Ratio" LINK ADV_RATIO}, @{"UserLevel" LINK ADV_LEVEL}, @{"Group/Location" LINK ADV_LOCATION}, @{"First Login" LINK ADV_FIRSTLOGIN}, @{"Last Login" LINK ADV_LASTLOGIN}
@endnode

@node "ADV_RATIO" "ADVANCED SEARCHING - CHECKMARK: Ratio"

                             @{u}CHECKMARK: Ratio@{uu}

                         @{i}(Advanced Search Window)@{ui}


Select this checkmark if you wish to search inside the @{b}Ratio@{ub} field of the
FAME user.datas. You don't have to worry about the conversation from integers
to strings, it will be all done automatically.

You have to specify at least one searching field to start the searching!

@{b}SEE ALSO:@{ub} @{"UserLevel" LINK ADV_LEVEL}, @{"Group/Location" LINK ADV_LOCATION}, @{"Conference Alias" LINK ADV_CONFACCESS}, @{"First Login" LINK ADV_FIRSTLOGIN}, @{"Last Login" LINK ADV_LASTLOGIN}
@endnode

@node "ADV_LEVEL" "ADVANCED SEARCHING - CHECKMARK: Level"

                             @{u}CHECKMARK: Level@{uu}

                         @{i}(Advanced Search Window)@{ui}


Select this checkmark if you wish to search inside the @{b}Userlevel@{ub} field of the
FAME user.datas. You don't have to worry about the conversation from integers
to strings, it will be all done automatically.

You have to specify at least one searching field to start the searching!

@{b}SEE ALSO:@{ub} @{"Ratio" LINK ADV_RATIO}, @{"Group/Location" LINK ADV_LOCATION}, @{"Conference Alias" LINK ADV_CONFACCESS}, @{"First Login" LINK ADV_FIRSTLOGIN}, @{"Last Login" LINK ADV_LASTLOGIN}
@endnode

@node "ADV_FIRSTLOGIN" "ADVANCED SEARCHING - CHECKMARK: First Login"

                          @{u}CHECKMARK: First Login@{uu}

                 @{i}(Advanced Search Window - New for V1.30)@{ui}

Select this checkmark if you wish to search inside the @{b}First Logindate@{ub} field
of the FAME user.datas. You may enter any valid date (MM-DD-YY) or a pattern
to search. 

Example: Searchstring is *98*

Results in showing all users which have first logged into your BBS in the year
1998.
You have to specify at least one searching field to start the searching!

@{b}SEE ALSO:@{ub} @{"Ratio" LINK ADV_RATIO}, @{"Group/Location" LINK ADV_LOCATION}, @{"Conference Alias" LINK ADV_CONFACCESS}, @{"Last Login" LINK ADV_LASTLOGIN}
@endnode

@node "ADV_LASTLOGIN" "ADVANCED SEARCHING - CHECKMARK: Last Login"

                           @{u}CHECKMARK: Last Login@{uu}

                 @{i}(Advanced Search Window - New for V1.30)@{ui}

Select this checkmark if you wish to search inside the @{b}Last Logindate@{ub} field
of the FAME user.datas. You may enter any valid date (MM-DD-YY) or a pattern
to search. 

Example: Searchstring is *98*

Results in showing all users which have last logged into your BBS in the year
1998.
You have to specify at least one searching field to start the searching!

@{b}SEE ALSO:@{ub} @{"Ratio" LINK ADV_RATIO}, @{"Group/Location" LINK ADV_LOCATION}, @{"Conference Alias" LINK ADV_CONFACCESS}, @{"First Login" LINK ADV_FIRSTLOGIN}
@endnode

@node "ADV_LV" "ADVANCED SEARCHING - LISTVIEW: Found Entries"

                          @{u}LISTVIEW: Found Entries@{uu}

                         @{i}(Advanced Search Window)@{ui}


The listview will be filled with all matching user.datas. After the searching
is finished, you could choose one of the found entries by double clicking on
it's entry. It will be loaded into UserEditor and the Main Window pops to
front. You may now alter any of the settings of the choosen user, or simply
bring back to front the Advanced Search Window to select one of the other
found entries. Both windows are working asynchronous for better overview.
@endnode

@node "ADV_START" "ADVANCED SEARCHING - BUTTON: Start Searching"

                           @{u}BUTTON: Start Search@{uu}

                         @{i}(Advanced Search Window)@{ui}


Click on this button to start the searching procedure. If any of the required
values are missing (no searchstring or no search fields activated), you will
get an errormessage. When starting the searching, UserEditor writes down
in the status line for which string it will search and all matching entries
will be added to the listview immediatly.
@endnode

@node "ADV_STOP" "ADVANCED SEARCHING - BUTTON: Cancel (Close Gadget)"

                     @{u}BUTTON: Cancel (or close gadget)@{uu}

                         @{i}(Advanced Search Window)@{ui}


This cancels the Advanced Searching and closes the window. You may also use
the '@{b}ESC@{ub}' key to close this window (or any other ;).
@endnode

@node "MUI" "MENU: PROJECT/About MUI-System"

                          This application uses


                        MUI - MagicUserInterface

                (c) Copyright 1993-98 by Stefan Stuntz


MUI is a system to generate and maintain graphical user interfaces. With the
aid  of  a  preferences program, the user of an application has the ability to
customize the outfit according to his personal taste.

MUI is distributed as shareware. To obtain a complete package containing lots
of examples and more information about registration please look for a  file
called  "muiXXusr.lha"  (XX means the latest version number) on your local
bulletin boards or on public domain disks.

          If you want to register directly, feel free to send


                         DM 30.-  or  US$ 20.-

                                  to

                             Stefan Stuntz
                        Eduard-Spranger-Straße 7
                             80935 München
                                GERMANY
@endnode

@node FABOUT "Informations about the FAME BBS System"

                          @{u}@{b}Informations about FAME@{uu}@{ub}

FAME is at this time still under construction, but because of the fact
that many people asked for FAME, it was released at the end of february 
1996 under the concept of shareware and will be available for everyone. 
At the begining not everything will be completly finished and because 
of this not everything you can already configure will work.

The registered Versions have to work at least some days before they will
be released for registered Users, but it's still possible that these 
versions also make problems when using them. But as soon as you've
reported those problems, they will be fixed!

If some of the settings won't work, it might be a bug but it's also (more)
possible that those functions are not implemented yet.

Some of the internal functions are currently untested and it's possible
that they produce errors or problems, but please remember the complexity
of FAME !

If you have questions or problems with FAME, please turn on one of the
FAME-Developers or ask Strider to solve your problems.


                         @{b}@{u}What should FAME costs ?@{ub}@{uu}

                            FAME Full version:  99 DM
                FAME & Doors from SieGeL/tRSi: 120 DM
                FAME & Doors from dr.Dre/tRSi: 120 DM
               FAME & Doors from SieGeL & Dre: 140 DM


                  @{b}@{u}What is included in the FAME-package ?@{ub}@{uu}

Server, SystemEditor, MainPart, FAMEHydra.FIM, FAMEError.FIM

FAME.library FAMEChat.FIM programmed by Bloodrock/tRSi

FAMEFullEd.FIM, FAMEScript.FIM programmed by Beatnik/tRSi

MUI UserEditor, FAMEDoorHelp.FIM, FAMEInfo programmed by SieGeL/tRSi

Also some doors and tools from the FAME-Development-Team are included,
but this doors are only unregistered Versions and have therefor some
limitations. The registered Versions of those doors and the Informations
how to get them are available here in the pUNISHMENT iNC. BBS.

It could happen that some of the doors and tools listed here are currently
missing because there are currently under development !


                            @{b}@{u}Who creates FAME ?@{ub}@{uu}

